  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 5 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 15 high, 8 medium, 16 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 12 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Craiova (CRA/LRCV), Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Cristiano Ronaldo (FNC/LPMA), Porto Santo (PXO/LPPS), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: thunderstorm / convective risk, low‑visibility procedures and RVR limitations. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Porto Santo (PXO/LPPS) and 9 others.",
